gomodel:SYNGO_25  a       owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: >5fold-enriched in docked SV fraction (fig. 5), 1.5fold enriched in glutamatergic synapses\nMS analysis after immunoisolation of synaptophysin (clone 7.2), VGLUT1 or VGAT positive synaptosomes\n\n18/01/2017 Pim/Frank+Gundelfinger lab\n- Important is that NP is 6x enriched in purified active zone compared to purified SVs. This means that NP is most likely localized in the active zone membrane. Note that NP is also found in SV membrane (Takamori et al. paper PMID:17110340).\n- NP has TM domain. Experimental description: Results: \"To isolate docking complexes from **rat brain**, we first prepared synaptosomes and subjected them to limited proteolysis to dissociate pre- and postsynaptic membranes (Figure 1A).\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099059 replaced by GO:0048787" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_25" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

